00:00:08.580 --> 00:00:11.500
Preparation of Selective and Differential
media

00:00:11.500 --> 00:00:19.090
A culture medium is a solid or liquid preparation
used to grow, transport, and store microorganisms.

00:00:19.090 --> 00:00:25.140
To be effective, the medium must contain all
the nutrients the microorganism requires for

00:00:25.140 --> 00:00:30.790
growth. Specialized media are essential in
the isolation and identification of microorganisms,

00:00:30.790 --> 00:00:36.840
the testing of antibiotic sensitivities, water
and food analysis, industrial microbiology,

00:00:36.840 --> 00:00:42.839
and other activities. In addition to nutrients
necessary for the growth of all bacteria,

00:00:42.839 --> 00:00:46.659
special-purpose media contain one or more
chemical compounds that are essential for

00:00:46.659 --> 00:00:53.280
their functional specificity.These includes
Selective media, Differential media and Enriched

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:54.280
media

00:00:54.280 --> 00:00:59.850
Selective media allow certain types of organisms
to grow, and inhibit the growth of other organisms.

00:00:59.850 --> 00:01:07.640
selective inhibition of some types of microorganisms
can be achieved by adding dyes, antibiotics,

00:01:07.640 --> 00:01:14.400
salts or specific inhibitors which affect
the metabolism or enzyme systems of the organisms.

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:22.561
Examples are Eosine Methylene Blue (EMB) agar,
Mannitol salt agar, Hektoen enteric agar (HE),

00:01:22.561 --> 00:01:26.940
Phenylethyl alcohol agar
Differential media are used to differentiate

00:01:26.940 --> 00:01:36.390
closely related organisms or groups of organismsEg;
MacConkey agar, Eosine Methylene Blue (EMB)

